---
layout: feature-kubernetes
title: GitLab Trust Center
description: At GitLab, we're committed to Information Security.
canonical_path: "/security/"
suppress_header: true
extra_css:
  - gitlab-feature-landing-page.css
  - security-trust.css
extra_js:
  - all-clickable.js
---

.wrapper.gitlab-ee-page
  .image-title
    .color-bg
      %div
        %h1 GitLab Trust Center
        -#%a.btn.btn-lg.btn-white{ href: "https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/integration/jira/", target: "_blank" } Documentation
  .sub-wrapper
    .container
      .row.advantages
        .col-xs-12.col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
          %p.security-trust-intro
            %strong At GitLab, we're committed to Information Security.
            It's our mission to be the leading example in security, innovation, and transparency.

      %hr.divider/

      .row.text-center
        .col-md-10.col-md-offset-1

          %h2 Compliance at GitLab

          %p.security-trust-sub-text #{link_to 'We take compliance seriously', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/security/security-assurance/security-compliance/sec-controls.html'}, because we know how much security, privacy and accessibility matters to our customers and stakeholders. 
          
          %p.security-trust-sub-text 
            %strong For detailed information on our Security and Compliance posture, see our #{link_to 'Customer Assurance Package', 'https://about.gitlab.com/security/cap/'}. 

      .row
        .col-md-5.col-md-offset-1
          .panel.panel-default.panel-margin
            .panel-heading
              %h3.panel-title SOC Certification
            .panel-body
              %div.security-trust-logo
                %img(src="/images/risk-and-field-security/SOC_NonCPA.jpg")
              %p.overview
                GitLab maintains #{link_to 'SOC 2 Type 2 and SOC 3', 'https://www.aicpa.org/interestareas/frc/assuranceadvisoryservices/serviceorganization-smanagement.html'} reports for the Security and Confidentiality Trust Services Criteria for the GitLab software-as-a-service (SaaS) platform.
  
        .col-md-5.col
          .panel.panel-default.panel-margin
            .panel-heading
              %h3.panel-title ISO/IEC 27001:2013 Certification
            .panel-body
              %div.security-trust-logo
                %img(src="/images/risk-and-field-security/ISO_27001_Logo.png")
              %p.overview
                GitLab maintains #{link_to 'ISO/IEC 27001:2013', 'https://www.schellman.com/certificate-directory?certificateNumber=1652216-1'} certification for the information security management system supporting the GitLab software-as-a-service (SaaS) platform.

      .row
        .col-md-5.col-md-offset-1
          .panel.panel-default.panel-margin
            .panel-heading
              %h3.panel-title VPAT Compliance
            .panel-body
              %div.security-trust-logo
                %img(src="/images/risk-and-field-security/vpat.jpg")
              %p.overview
                GitLab's #{link_to 'Accessibility Conformance Report', 'https://design.gitlab.com/accessibility/vpat'} shows our commitment to maintaining a product where everyone can contribute.

        .col-md-5
          .panel.panel-default.panel-margin
            .panel-heading
              %h3.panel-title GDPR Compliance
            .panel-body
              %div.security-trust-logo
                %img(src="/images/risk-and-field-security/gdpr.jpg")
              %p.overview
                GitLab is compliant with #{link_to 'GDPR requirements', '/privacy/privacy-compliance/'}.

      .row
        .col-md-5.col-md-offset-1
          .panel.panel-default.panel-margin
            .panel-heading
              %h3.panel-title Bitsight Security Rating
            .panel-body
              %div.security-trust-logo
                %img(src="/images/risk-and-field-security/BitSight_Logo_Tagline.png")
              %p.overview
                GitLab maintains an advanced #{link_to 'Bitsight security rating', 'https://about.gitlab.com/blog/2020/12/18/how-gitlab-uses-third-party-security-ratings-to-build-customer-confidence/'} for our production environment.

        .col-md-5
          .panel.panel-default.panel-margin
            .panel-heading
              %h3.panel-title CSA Trusted Cloud Provider
            .panel-body
              %div.security-trust-logo
                %img(src="/images/risk-and-field-security/CSA_Trusted_Cloud_Provider_badge.png")
              %p.overview
                GitLab is a #{link_to 'Cloud Security Alliance (CSA) Trusted Cloud Provider', 'https://cloudsecurityalliance.org/star/registry/gitlab/'}. 

.row.security-trust-card-group
  .card.security-trust-card
    .card-body.security-trust-card-body
      %h4.card-title.security-trust-title Security
      %p.card-text
        %ul.security-trust-list
          %li #{link_to 'Frequently asked questions (FAQs)', '/security/faq/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Our security practices', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/security/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Best practices for securing your GitLab instance', 'https://about.gitlab.com/blog/2020/05/20/gitlab-instance-security-best-practices/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Security blog', 'https://about.gitlab.com/blog/categories/security/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Security department overview', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/security/'}

  .card.security-trust-card
    .card-body.security-trust-card-body
      %h4.card-title.security-trust-title Privacy
      %p.card-text
        %ul.security-trust-list
          %li #{link_to 'Frequently asked questions (FAQs)', '/privacy/2021-update-faq/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Privacy policy', '/privacy/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Personal data requests', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/gdpr/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Responsible disclosure policy', '/security/disclosure/'}
          %li #{link_to 'GitLab privacy processes', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/legal/privacy/'}

  .card.security-trust-card
    .card-body.security-trust-card-body
      %h4.card-title.security-trust-title Availability
      %p.card-text
        %ul.security-trust-list
          %li #{link_to 'Frequently asked questions (FAQs)', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/engineering/infrastructure/faq/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Monitoring of GitLab.com', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/engineering/monitoring/'}
          %li #{link_to 'GitLab.com production architecture', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/engineering/infrastructure/production/architecture/'}
          %li #{link_to 'GitLab releases', 'https://about.gitlab.com/releases/'}
          %li #{link_to 'Infrastructure department overview', 'https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/engineering/infrastructure/'}

.row.text-center
  .col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
    = link_to "Contact our Security Team", "mailto:customer-assurance@gitlab.com", class: "btn cta-btn accent"
    
.row.text-center
  .col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
    %p
      %br>/
      To sign up for Security Notices, visit the
      %a{:href => "https://about.gitlab.com/company/contact/"} Sign up for security notices
